<li><a href="http://www.bmcfullyawake.org" class="external text" title="http://www.bmcfullyawake.org" rel="nofollow">Fully Awake: Black Mountain College Documentary</a> the only documentary solely on Black Mountain College. The story of BMC is woven through interviews with students, professors and modern scholars with archival footage and photographs.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.journalnow.com/servlet/Satellite?pagename=WSJ/MGArticle/WSJ_RelishArticle&amp;c=MGArticle&amp;cid=1149189298208" class="external text" title="http://www.journalnow.com/servlet/Satellite?pagename=WSJ/MGArticle/WSJ_RelishArticle&amp;c=MGArticle&amp;cid=1149189298208" rel="nofollow"><i>Honoring the Mind's Eye</i></a> article on Hazel Larsen Archer, a photographer who documented her years at the college in the 1940s and early '50s</li>
<li><a href="http://www.mindspring.com/~cliofilm" class="external text" title="http://www.mindspring.com/~cliofilm" rel="nofollow">Bauhaus in America</a> a documentary about the influence of the Bauhaus on America, including a segment on Black Mountain College with Anni Albers, Ted and Bobbi Dreier, <i>et alia.</i> produced and directed by Judith Pearlman, Cliofilm.</li>
<li><a href="http://blackmountaincollegecelebration.com/" class="external text" title="http://blackmountaincollegecelebration.com/" rel="nofollow">Black Mountain College Celebration</a> 75th Anniversary of Black Mountain College</li>
